Spring security defines a framework for security
Implemented using filters in bacgground
Two methods-
declarative and Programatic

Declarative-
 Define applications security constraints in configuration
 All java config(@Configuration)
 or Spring XML
 Provides separation of concerns betw application code and security code
 
Programatic security-
Spring provides API for custom application coding
Provides greater customization for your specific app requirement

Diff Login Methods Spring provide
1.Http Basic authentication
2.Default login form provided by spring security
3.Custom login form

Authentication and AUthorization
  In-memory
  JDBC
  LDAP
  Custom/Plugable
  
  
